    • Method Detail

      • createOrFindTestCaseWorkItem

        IWorkItem createOrFindTestCaseWorkItem(java.lang.String projectId,
                                       java.lang.String testCaseId,
                                       IWorkItem template)
        Finds Work Item in specified project with type specified by TestsConfiguration.getTestCaseWorkItemType() having the same value in the custom field specified by TestsConfiguration.getTestCaseIdCustomField() as the testCaseId parameter. When there is not such Work Item, than the method creates new Work Item and sets the value of testCaseId parameter to above mentioned custom field.
        Parameters:
        projectId - id project in which the Work Item should be searched/created.
        testCaseId - id of the test case for example from xUnit file, not the ID of the Work Item
        template - when null then template from configuration is used
        Returns:
        never returns null or unresolvable Work Item.
        See Also:
        isAutomatedTestCase(IWorkItem)

      • isAutomatedTestCase

        boolean isAutomatedTestCase(IWorkItem workItem)
        Checks if the given Work Item was created by createOrFindTestCaseWorkItem(String, String, IWorkItem) method by checking if it has not empty custom field which is filled by the createOrFindTestCaseWorkItem(String, String, IWorkItem) method
        See Also:
        createOrFindTestCaseWorkItem(String, String, IWorkItem)
